sbsbofh wrote:
&gt; I have a job that is getting very large, the partition that Heritrix
&gt; lives on will get full soon.  I have paused the job.
&gt;
&gt; I would like to shut down Heritrix, and move the entire installation
&gt; to a larger partition, restart Heritrix, and continue with the job. 
&gt;
&gt; It&#39;s not clear to me whether this will work!  Do paused jobs survive
&gt; restarting the engine?
They do not. 

You need to checkpoint and then in the new location, do a recovery from 
the checkpoint made at end-of-crawl.  See section 9.4, &quot;Checkpointing&quot; 
in the user manual: 
http://crawler.archive.org/articles/user_manual.html#checkpoint. 

Checkpointing is a new feature of 1.6.  If using an earlier version, see 
section 9.3 &quot;Recovery of Frontier State and recover.gz&quot;.

Yours,
St.Ack


